tip.text: Very decent barbecue. The other reviews are actually true about the pork being really good! We ordered the pork cheek - tender,tasty, without an over-abundance of fat. Seafood pancake worth it too.

Hands-down the best Udon I've ever had, without exaggeration. I had the "Fish paste & soft-boiled egg tempura Bukkake" udon, a side of raw egg and mentaiko. All dishes ordered were fresh and v. tasty.
